{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":359,"text":"Hi. I am an architect."},{"time":2008,"text":"I am the only architect in the world"},{"time":4456,"text":"making buildings out of paper like this cardboard tube,"},{"time":7772,"text":"and this exhibition is the first one I did"},{"time":10338,"text":"using paper tubes."},{"time":11846,"text":"1986, much, much longer before people started talking"},{"time":16271,"text":"about ecological issues and environmental issues,"},{"time":20474,"text":"I just started testing the paper tube"},{"time":23764,"text":"in order to use this as a building structure."},{"time":26499,"text":"It's very complicated to test the new material for the building,"},{"time":31652,"text":"but this is much stronger than I expected,"},{"time":34150,"text":"and also it's very easy to waterproof,"},{"time":36362,"text":"and also, because it's industrial material,"},{"time":38257,"text":"it's also possible to fireproof."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40960,"text":"Then I built the temporary structure, 1990."},{"time":44793,"text":"This is the first temporary building made out of paper."},{"time":47800,"text":"There are 330 tubes, diameter 55 [centimeters],"},{"time":51870,"text":"there are only 12 tubes with a diameter"},{"time":53512,"text":"of 120 centimeters, or four feet, wide."},{"time":56282,"text":"As you see it in the photo, inside is the toilet."},{"time":58902,"text":"In case you're finished with toilet paper,"},{"time":61553,"text":"you can tear off the inside of the wall. (Laughter)"},{"time":63873,"text":"So it's very useful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66265,"text":"Year 2000, there was a big expo in Germany."},{"time":70304,"text":"I was asked to design the building,"},{"time":72923,"text":"because the theme of the expo was environmental issues."},{"time":75717,"text":"So I was chosen to build the pavilion out of paper tubes,"},{"time":80205,"text":"recyclable paper."},{"time":81932,"text":"My goal of the design is not when it's completed."},{"time":84902,"text":"My goal was when the building was demolished,"},{"time":86986,"text":"because each country makes a lot of pavilions"},{"time":90962,"text":"but after half a year, we create a lot of industrial waste,"},{"time":94062,"text":"so my building has to be reused or recycled."},{"time":98743,"text":"After, the building was recycled."},{"time":100846,"text":"So that was the goal of my design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103492,"text":"Then I was very lucky to win the competition"},{"time":106580,"text":"to build the second Pompidou Center in France"},{"time":109238,"text":"in the city of Metz."},{"time":110713,"text":"Because I was so poor,"},{"time":112209,"text":"I wanted to rent an office in Paris,"},{"time":114376,"text":"but I couldn't afford it,"},{"time":115893,"text":"so I decided to bring my students to Paris"},{"time":117934,"text":"to build our office on top of the Pompidou Center in Paris"},{"time":121450,"text":"by ourselves."},{"time":122685,"text":"So we brought the paper tubes and the wooden joints"},{"time":126014,"text":"to complete the 35-meter-long office."},{"time":130099,"text":"We stayed there for six years without paying any rent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133133,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":137004,"text":"Thank you. I had one big problem."},{"time":139391,"text":"Because we were part of the exhibition,"},{"time":141745,"text":"even if my friend wanted to see me, they had to buy a ticket to see me."},{"time":145049,"text":"That was the problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147252,"text":"Then I completed the Pompidou Center in Metz."},{"time":150020,"text":"It's a very popular museum now,"},{"time":151974,"text":"and I created a big monument for the government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155140,"text":"But then I was very disappointed"},{"time":157039,"text":"at my profession as an architect,"},{"time":159635,"text":"because we are not helping, we are not working for society,"},{"time":163663,"text":"but we are working for privileged people,"},{"time":166907,"text":"rich people, government, developers."},{"time":170099,"text":"They have money and power."},{"time":172619,"text":"Those are invisible."},{"time":174416,"text":"So they hire us to visualize their power and money"},{"time":178244,"text":"by making monumental architecture."},{"time":180477,"text":"That is our profession, even historically it's the same,"},{"time":182642,"text":"even now we are doing the same."},{"time":184994,"text":"So I was very disappointed that we are not working for society,"},{"time":188318,"text":"even though there are so many people"},{"time":192320,"text":"who lost their houses by natural disasters."},{"time":195212,"text":"But I must say they are no longer natural disasters."},{"time":198255,"text":"For example, earthquakes never kill people,"},{"time":201240,"text":"but collapse of the buildings kill people."},{"time":203413,"text":"That's the responsibility of architects."},{"time":205453,"text":"Then people need some temporary housing,"},{"time":207190,"text":"but there are no architects working there"},{"time":208852,"text":"because we are too busy working for privileged people."},{"time":212512,"text":"So I thought, even as architects,"},{"time":216391,"text":"we can be involved in the reconstruction of temporary housing."},{"time":221147,"text":"We can make it better."},{"time":222939,"text":"So that is why I started working in disaster areas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226972,"text":"1994, there was a big disaster in Rwanda, Africa."},{"time":230698,"text":"Two tribes, Hutu and Tutsi, fought each other."},{"time":233430,"text":"Over two million people became refugees."},{"time":235928,"text":"But I was so surprised to see the shelter, refugee camp"},{"time":239679,"text":"organized by the U.N."},{"time":241913,"text":"They're so poor, and they are freezing"},{"time":245207,"text":"with blankets during the rainy season,"},{"time":247330,"text":"In the shelters built by the U.N.,"},{"time":250085,"text":"they were just providing a plastic sheet,"},{"time":252391,"text":"and the refugees had to cut the trees, and just like this."},{"time":256540,"text":"But over two million people cut trees."},{"time":258306,"text":"It just became big, heavy deforestation"},{"time":261097,"text":"and an environmental problem."},{"time":262830,"text":"That is why they started providing aluminum pipes, aluminum barracks."},{"time":266060,"text":"Very expensive, they throw them out for money,"},{"time":268347,"text":"then cutting trees again."},{"time":270273,"text":"So I proposed my idea to improve the situation"},{"time":274294,"text":"using these recycled paper tubes"},{"time":276454,"text":"because this is so cheap and also so strong,"},{"time":279387,"text":"but my budget is only 50 U.S. dollars per unit."},{"time":282134,"text":"We built 50 units to do that as a monitoring test"},{"time":285095,"text":"for the durability and moisture and termites, so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290801,"text":"And then, year afterward, 1995, in Kobe, Japan,"},{"time":295381,"text":"we had a big earthquake."},{"time":297174,"text":"Nearly 7,000 people were killed,"},{"time":299686,"text":"and the city like this Nagata district,"},{"time":302677,"text":"all the city was burned in a fire after the earthquake."},{"time":305995,"text":"And also I found out there's many Vietnamese refugees"},{"time":309936,"text":"suffering and gathering at a Catholic church --"},{"time":312531,"text":"all the building was totally destroyed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314450,"text":"So I went there and also I proposed to the priests,"},{"time":317951,"text":"\"Why don't we rebuild the church out of paper tubes?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":320569,"text":"And he said, \"Oh God, are you crazy?"},{"time":323709,"text":"After a fire, what are you proposing?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":325818,"text":"So he never trusted me, but I didn't give up."},{"time":329446,"text":"I started commuting to Kobe,"},{"time":331328,"text":"and I met the society of Vietnamese people."},{"time":333957,"text":"They were living like this with very poor plastic sheets"},{"time":336624,"text":"in the park."},{"time":337905,"text":"So I proposed to rebuild. I raised -- did fundraising."},{"time":341147,"text":"I made a paper tube shelter for them,"},{"time":343703,"text":"and in order to make it easy to be built by students"},{"time":346661,"text":"and also easy to demolish,"},{"time":348244,"text":"I used beer crates as a foundation."},{"time":351453,"text":"I asked the Kirin beer company to propose,"},{"time":354043,"text":"because at that time, the Asahi beer company"},{"time":356763,"text":"made their plastic beer crates red,"},{"time":358775,"text":"which doesn't go with the color of the paper tubes."},{"time":361189,"text":"The color coordination is very important."},{"time":363507,"text":"And also I still remember, we were expecting"},{"time":366700,"text":"to have a beer inside the plastic beer crate,"},{"time":369055,"text":"but it came empty. (Laughter)"},{"time":370949,"text":"So I remember it was so disappointing."},{"time":374341,"text":"So during the summer with my students,"},{"time":376579,"text":"we built over 50 units of the shelters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378765,"text":"Finally the priest, finally he trusted me to rebuild."},{"time":381536,"text":"He said, \"As long as you collect money by yourself,"},{"time":383827,"text":"bring your students to build, you can do it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":386081,"text":"So we spent five weeks rebuilding the church."},{"time":388564,"text":"It was meant to stay there for three years,"},{"time":392062,"text":"but actually it stayed there 10 years because people loved it."},{"time":395360,"text":"Then, in Taiwan, they had a big earthquake,"},{"time":399169,"text":"and we proposed to donate this church,"},{"time":403119,"text":"so we dismantled them,"},{"time":404720,"text":"we sent them over to be built by volunteer people."},{"time":406965,"text":"It stayed there in Taiwan as a permanent church even now."},{"time":410589,"text":"So this building became a permanent building."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413080,"text":"Then I wonder, what is a permanent and what is a temporary building?"},{"time":417729,"text":"Even a building made in paper"},{"time":419662,"text":"can be permanent as long as people love it."},{"time":423192,"text":"Even a concrete building can be very temporary"},{"time":425488,"text":"if that is made to make money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427505,"text":"In 1999, in Turkey, the big earthquake,"},{"time":430215,"text":"I went there to use the local material to build a shelter."},{"time":434365,"text":"2001, in West India, I built also a shelter."},{"time":438219,"text":"In 2004, in Sri Lanka, after the Sumatra earthquake"},{"time":442300,"text":"and tsunami, I rebuilt Islamic fishermen's villages."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445981,"text":"And in 2008, in Chengdu, Sichuan area in China,"},{"time":451432,"text":"nearly 70,000 people were killed,"},{"time":454358,"text":"and also especially many of the schools were destroyed"},{"time":457443,"text":"because of the corruption between the authority and the contractor."},{"time":460893,"text":"I was asked to rebuild the temporary church."},{"time":463861,"text":"I brought my Japanese students to work with the Chinese students."},{"time":467647,"text":"In one month, we completed nine classrooms,"},{"time":470508,"text":"over 500 square meters."},{"time":472160,"text":"It's still used, even after the current earthquake in China."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476632,"text":"In 2009, in Italy, L'Aquila, also they had a big earthquake."},{"time":482096,"text":"And this is a very interesting photo:"},{"time":484448,"text":"former Prime Minister Berlusconi"},{"time":487165,"text":"and Japanese former former former former Prime Minister Mr. Aso --"},{"time":491583,"text":"you know, because we have to change the prime minister ever year."},{"time":495464,"text":"And they are very kind, affording my model."},{"time":500426,"text":"I proposed a big rebuilding, a temporary music hall,"},{"time":504825,"text":"because L'Aquila is very famous for music"},{"time":507269,"text":"and all the concert halls were destroyed,"},{"time":508694,"text":"so musicians were moving out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510826,"text":"So I proposed to the mayor,"},{"time":512253,"text":"I'd like to rebuild the temporary auditorium."},{"time":514488,"text":"He said, \"As long as you bring your money, you can do it.\""},{"time":517434,"text":"And I was very lucky."},{"time":518617,"text":"Mr. Berlusconi brought G8 summit,"},{"time":520918,"text":"and our former prime minister came,"},{"time":523024,"text":"so they helped us to collect money,"},{"time":526229,"text":"and I got half a million euros from the Japanese government"},{"time":529072,"text":"to rebuild this temporary auditorium."}]},{"cues":[{"time":531959,"text":"Year 2010 in Haiti, there was a big earthquake,"},{"time":536679,"text":"but it's impossible to fly over,"},{"time":538270,"text":"so I went to Santo Domingo, next-door country,"},{"time":541287,"text":"to drive six hours to get to Haiti"},{"time":544202,"text":"with the local students in Santo Domingo"},{"time":547493,"text":"to build 50 units of shelter out of local paper tubes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550946,"text":"This is what happened in Japan two years ago, in northern Japan."},{"time":554559,"text":"After the earthquake and tsunami,"},{"time":556434,"text":"people had to be evacuated in a big room like a gymnasium."},{"time":560221,"text":"But look at this. There's no privacy."},{"time":562122,"text":"People suffer mentally and physically."},{"time":564989,"text":"So we went there to build partitions"},{"time":568380,"text":"with all the student volunteers with paper tubes,"},{"time":571643,"text":"just a very simple shelter out of the tube frame and the curtain."},{"time":575874,"text":"However, some of the facility authority"},{"time":578390,"text":"doesn't want us to do it, because, they said,"},{"time":580437,"text":"simply, it's become more difficult to control them."},{"time":583634,"text":"But it's really necessary to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":586116,"text":"They don't have enough flat area to build"},{"time":588621,"text":"standard government single-story housing like this one."},{"time":591906,"text":"Look at this. Even civil government is doing"},{"time":594156,"text":"such poor construction of the temporary housing,"},{"time":598285,"text":"so dense and so messy because there is no storage, nothing, water is leaking,"},{"time":604816,"text":"so I thought, we have to make multi-story building"},{"time":608085,"text":"because there's no land and also it's not very comfortable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611110,"text":"So I proposed to the mayor while I was making partitions."},{"time":616040,"text":"Finally I met a very nice mayor in Onagawa village"},{"time":619671,"text":"in Miyagi."},{"time":620991,"text":"He asked me to build three-story housing on baseball [fields]."},{"time":625377,"text":"I used the shipping container"},{"time":628103,"text":"and also the students helped us to make"},{"time":630556,"text":"all the building furniture"},{"time":633354,"text":"to make them comfortable,"},{"time":635046,"text":"within the budget of the government"},{"time":637321,"text":"but also the area of the house is exactly the same,"},{"time":641230,"text":"but much more comfortable."},{"time":642370,"text":"Many of the people want to stay here forever."},{"time":645502,"text":"I was very happy to hear that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648064,"text":"Now I am working in New Zealand, Christchurch."},{"time":652001,"text":"About 20 days before the Japanese earthquake happened,"},{"time":655848,"text":"also they had a big earthquake,"},{"time":657353,"text":"and many Japanese students were also killed,"},{"time":659914,"text":"and the most important cathedral of the city,"},{"time":662233,"text":"the symbol of Christchurch, was totally destroyed."},{"time":665004,"text":"And I was asked to come to rebuild the temporary cathedral."}]},{"cues":[{"time":669102,"text":"So this is under construction."},{"time":671389,"text":"And I'd like to keep building monuments"},{"time":674729,"text":"that are beloved by people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676959,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678398,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":680334,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":683067,"text":"Thank you very much. (Applause)"}]}]}